---
title: Curried Chickpea Burgers with Tomatoes, Tangy Mayo & Roasted Potato Wedges
description: We LOVE a burger, and we know you do too! Luckily our chefs know how to keep the romance alive. These swoony chickpea burgers are packed with fragrant curry powder, scallions, and dill. They’re pan-fried until crisp on the outside and tender on the inside, then tucked onto buttery toasted buns, slathered with tangy apricot-Dijon mayo and juicy tomato slices. This charmer comes with roasted potato wedges on the side because we heart you.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/curried-chickpea-burgers-c4b65614.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/curried-chickpea-burgers-6345a878ae5691a5b70f3102-c54c9cb1.pdf
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: Middle East
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 940 kcal
  fat: 47 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 115 g
  sugar: 25 g
  protein: 12 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 1590 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/curried-chickpea-burgers-6345a878ae5691a5b70f3102
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring @butter{1%tbsp} to room temperature. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Peel and mince @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens; mince whites. Pick and mince fronds from @dill{¼%ounce}(minced). Thinly slice @tomato{1}(thinly sliced) and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Tangy Mayo ==

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @mayonnaise{4%tbsp}, @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, @apricot jam{1%unit}, half the @turmeric{1%tsp} (all for 4 servings), and 2 tsp @white wine vinegar{5%tsp} (4 tsp for 4) until combined. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

> Be sure to measure the vinegar—we sent more.

== Chickpea Patties ==

Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%unit}. Place half the chickpeas (all for 4 servings) in a #large bowl{}. Mash with a #potato masher{} or fork until almost smooth.

> TIP: It's OK if there are some larger pieces.

Stir in garlic, scallion whites, half the scallion greens, half the dill, half the @curry powder{1%tbsp}, 3 TBSP @tempura batter{82%g} mix (be sure to measure; we sent more), and 2 TBSP water until thoroughly combined. Taste and season with salt (we used ¼ tsp; ½ tsp for 4) and pepper.

Divide chickpea mixture into two mounds (four mounds for 4).

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Using a #silicone spatula{}, add chickpea mounds to pan and gently press to flatten into patties (rub a little oil on the bottom of the spatula to prevent sticking), each about as wide as a burger bun. Cook until golden brown and crisp, ~{3-4%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #plate{}.

> TIP: Add more oil when flipping the patties if needed.

== Assembly ==

Meanwhile, halve and toast @brioche buns{2} until golden; spread softened butter onto cut sides of bottom buns.

Spread top buns with as much tangy mayo as you like. Fill buns with chickpea patties and tomato.

Divide chickpea burgers and potato wedges between plates. Sprinkle potatoes with remaining scallion greens and remaining dill. Serve with remaining tangy mayo on the side for dipping.